<Layout title="About HostFleet — methodology">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-24 prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>HostFleet is an independent review site focused on the platforms developers and AI builders actually deploy to in 2026 — GPU inference hosts (Runpod, Modal, Fal, Replicate, Baseten), edge runtimes (Vercel, Cloudflare, Netlify, Fly), and the destinations where AI-generated sites from Lovable, Bolt, and v0 land in production.</p>
    <h2>Editor</h2>
    <p><strong>Alex Harmon</strong> — Senior Infrastructure Analyst. Alex is an AI-assisted byline backed by a research and benchmarking pipeline that runs continuous deploys against the platforms we cover.</p>
    <h2>How we test</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Real deploys, not vendor docs. Cold-start, latency, and cost numbers come from live workloads.</li>
      <li>Identical workload across competitors. We publish the workload definition with each comparison.</li>
      <li>Re-run on a schedule. Numbers carry the date they were captured.</li>
      <li>Affiliate disclosure on every page. Some outbound links pay a commission. Methodology and conclusions are not for sale.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><a href="mailto:hostfleet@aumedia.sk">hostfleet@aumedia.sk</a></p>
